# How to set up PHP Storm debugger with X-Debug

1. Set up php executable - Settings->PHP (enter path to php executable)
2. Set up php.ini for selected interpreter - find apropirate php.ini file and add following
	[xdebug]
	zend_extension="/path/to/xdebug/module" (comes preinstaled with MAMP)
	xdebug.remote_enable=1
	xdebug.remote_host=localhost
	xdebug.remote_port=9000
3. Refresh button in PHP storm settings next to field for entering path to php executable (step 1)
4. Restart server
5. Enable Debugging in browser (Debugg plugin in chrome (green bug at the right side of search field))
6. Set up Run/Debug configurationtions (top center part of PHP Storm IDE)
7. Start listening PHP Storm (phone icon next to Run/Debug configuration)